def snowball_sampling(graph, start_node, max_nodes=10000, max_depth=5):
    sampled_nodes = set()
    frontier = set([start_node])
    depth = 0

    while frontier and len(sampled_nodes) < max_nodes and depth <= max_depth:
        next_frontier = set()
        for node in frontier:
            if node not in sampled_nodes:
                sampled_nodes.add(node)
                neighbors = set(graph.neighbors(node))
                next_frontier.update(neighbors - sampled_nodes)
        frontier = next_frontier
        depth += 1

import networkx as nx

#  G 
# 
degree_centrality = nx.degree_centrality(G)

# 
max_centrality = max(degree_centrality.values())
candidates = [node for node, centrality in degree_centrality.items() if centrality == max_centrality]

# 
start_node = random.choice(candidates)

# 
def snowball_sampling(graph, start_node, max_nodes=10000, max_depth=5): 
    visited = set()
    queue = [(start_node, 0)]
    
    while queue and len(visited) < max_nodes:
        current_node, depth = queue.pop(0)
        if current_node not in visited and depth <= max_depth:
            visited.add(current_node)
            neighbors = graph.neighbors(current_node)
            for neighbor in neighbors:
                if neighbor not in visited:
                    queue.append((neighbor, depth + 1))
    return graph.subgraph(visited)

sampled_G = snowball_sampling(G, start_node, max_nodes=10000, max_depth=5)

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))  
nx.draw(sampled_G, with_labels=False, node_size=20, node_color='skyblue', edge_color='gray')
plt.title('Snowball Sampled Subgraph-Start from Highest Degree Centrality Node')
plt.show()

from scipy.optimize import minimize_scalar
import community as community_louvain
import networkx as nx

def objective(resolution):
    # 
    partition = community_louvain.best_partition(sampled_G, resolution=resolution)
    return -community_louvain.modularity(partition, sampled_G)

# 
result = minimize_scalar(objective, bounds=(0.1, 3.0), method='bounded')

# 
best_resolution = result.x
best_partition = community_louvain.best_partition(sampled_G, resolution=best_resolution)
best_modularity = community_louvain.modularity(best_partition, sampled_G)

print("Best Resolution:", best_resolution)
print("Best Modularity:", best_modularity)
print("Best Community Count:", len(set(best_partition.values())))

# 
nx.draw(sampled_G, 
        cmap=plt.get_cmap('viridis'), 
        node_color=list(best_partition.values()), 
        with_labels=False, 
        node_size=200)
plt.show()

import random
import networkx as nx
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# 
def snowball_sampling(graph, start_node, max_nodes=10000, max_depth=5):
    sampled_nodes = set()
    frontier = set([start_node])
    depth = 0 

    while frontier and len(sampled_nodes) < max_nodes and depth <= max_depth:
        next_frontier = set()
        for node in frontier:
            if node not in sampled_nodes:
                sampled_nodes.add(node)
                neighbors = set(graph.neighbors(node))
                next_frontier.update(neighbors - sampled_nodes)
        frontier = next_frontier
        depth += 1

    # 
    subgraph = graph.subgraph(sampled_nodes).copy()
    return subgraph

# 1020
num_start_nodes = random.randint(10, 20)  # 10-20
start_nodes = random.sample(list(G.nodes()), num_start_nodes)

# 
all_sampled_nodes = set()

# 
for start_node in start_nodes:
    sampled_subgraph = snowball_sampling(G, start_node, max_nodes=10000, max_depth=5)
    all_sampled_nodes.update(sampled_subgraph.nodes())

# 
final_subgraph = G.subgraph(all_sampled_nodes).copy()

# 
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
nx.draw(final_subgraph, with_labels=False, node_size=20, node_color='skyblue', edge_color='gray')
plt.title('Multi-start Snowball Sampled Subgraph')
plt.show()
